## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0758-102">Quand ils sont déclenchés, la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> et <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> événements passent une instance de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> au gestionnaire pour l’événement associé.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0758-102">When they are raised, the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> events pass an instance of  <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> to  the handler for the associated event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0758-103">Le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs.AudioLevel%2A> property get, le nouveau niveau de son entrée quand le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> ou <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> événement est déclenché.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0758-103">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs.AudioLevel%2A> property gets the new level of audio input when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> event is raised.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0758-104">Le `AudioLevel` propriété de la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> et <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> classes fournit le niveau actuel de l’entrée audio pour le moteur de reconnaissance vocale.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0758-104">The `AudioLevel` property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> classes provides the current level of the audio input to the speech recognition engine.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0758-105">L’exemple suivant ajoute un gestionnaire d’événements à un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> objet.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0758-105">The following example adds an event handler to a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0758-106">Le gestionnaire génère le nouveau niveau audio à la console.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0758-106">The handler outputs the new audio level to the console.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0758-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> dérive de <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0758-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the SpeechRecognitionEngine object.   
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add an event handler for the AudioLevelUpdated event.  
  sre.AudioLevelUpdated += new EventHandler<AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs>(sre_AudioLevelUpdated);  
  
  // Add other initialization code here.  
}  
  
// Write the audio level to the console when the AudioLevelUpdated event is raised.  
void sre_AudioLevelUpdated(object sender, AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs e)  
{  
  Console.WriteLine("The audio level is now: {0}.", e.AudioLevel);  
}  
  
```
